step 1) ssh to the Linux server as root
step 2)  vi  /etc/init.d/kafka-manager  
  -- use the file @ https://github.com/datteswararao/kafka-manager/blob/master/scripts/kafka-manager
Step 3) chmod 755 /etc/init.d/kafka-manager
Step 4) chkconfig --add kafka-manager
Step 5) chkconfig kafka-manager on
Step 6) test below
sudo service kafka-manager start
sudo service kafka-manager status
sudo service kafka-manager stop
sudo service kafka-manager restart
Step 7) reboot
Step 8) see the service starts at bootstrap of the instance or server.
